<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Operator. Strategist. Building infrastructure for smallholder supply chains."
	pubDate={new Date('Apr 25 2026')}
>
	<p>
		I'm Nikhil Pradhan. I build operational infrastructure for places spreadsheets
		forgot.
	</p>
	<p>
		Since 2020 I've been CEO of <strong>ApiCare</strong>, an agri-tech venture
		operating in Sikkim — India's only fully organic state. We work with 125+
		smallholder beekeepers and farmers across three Himalayan districts under a
		World Bank RAMP partnership with the Government of Sikkim. Our supply chain
		has cleared three KPMG audit cycles with zero findings and we are building
		toward an EU export pipeline.
	</p>
	<p>
		In 2025 I joined the Erasmus Mundus MBA program in Impact Entrepreneurship
		(EMMIE) — a fellowship that's taken me from Zagreb to Vilnius and, in
		September 2026, on to Liège. I graduate in December 2026.
	</p>
	<p>
		Alongside the MBA, I'm building <strong>FarmLedger</strong> — a WhatsApp-native
		AI traceability and credit-profile platform for the world's smallest farms.
		Multimodal AI extracts data from farmer-submitted photos to generate credit
		profiles a bank can underwrite against. The work sits at the intersection of
		traceability infrastructure, smallholder finance, and the kind of supply-chain
		transparency that EUDR will require by 2027. FarmLedger closed its first
		$15K seed round in 2026.
	</p>
	<h2>What's next</h2>
	<p>
		I'm moving toward Strategy &amp; Operations roles at platform companies in
		Europe — marketplaces, fintech, and logistics platforms where the work is
		dense and the problems are operational at scale. I want to bring five years
		of operator instinct to teams building products that survive contact with
		reality. Graduating December 2026, EU work-eligible, open to conversations
		now.
	</p>
